July 23, 2016 at 4:40 PM ¬∑

Every now and then when the world seems like it's getn out of hand again I like to post this song we did at Birdmans studio in Miami,out of nowhere in one take we just started playing and Bryce started singing and Smoking Mirrors was born during the Anthrax Scare. Never was on any CD but always comes to Heart during times as these. We Are All One, What The World Needs Now "LOVE" Bryce A Rutkowski Mackie Cleveland Patrick Clay Boxelder Sean Birdman Gould

post_text:
Friends, fans, and music lovers‚Ä¶

Would you be willing to spend 4 days on a beautiful cruise ship with us and an all star line up of bands? Boxelder is a huge fan of Rockboat and we are trying to get onboard.

Although we are not currently booked on the bill, we are putting it out there to get an idea if our people would be into
it. If you aren‚Äôt familiar with Rockboat do yourself a favor and visit www.therockboat.com . It is the most fun you will ever have without breaking the law‚Ä¶.a true adult dose!

This year celebrates 14 successful years of killer music and unreal times on the sea. Rockboat XIV cruises from Miami to Great Stirrup Cay on the Norweigan Pearl Feb. 22-26. Rates start at $399 per person. If Boxelder was onboard would you join us?

Let us know in the comments...
